      run.addBreak();
      run.setText(&quot;Tank repressurisation would be done &quot; + tank_Repressurisation_Chosen);
    ...

But more Word-lke is to use an additional paragraph for each time you would press &lt;kbd&gt;Enter&lt;/kbd&gt; in Word&#39;s GUI. Word also adds a new paragraph when the user press &lt;kbd&gt;Enter&lt;/kbd&gt; in Word&#39;s GUI.

Using different single `XWPFRun` per text run is also better for formatting later. All needed different text formatting needs their own `XWPFRun`.

If the need is to append data into the same file each time the code runs, then we need check whether the file already exists and, if so, create the `XWPFDocument` from that file. To do so constructor [public XWPFDocument(java.io.InputStream is)](https://poi.apache.org/apidocs/dev/org/apache/poi/xwpf/usermodel/XWPFDocument.html#XWPFDocument-java.io.InputStream-) can be used.

